article.headline: Princeton 60, Dominican, N.Y. 46
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) -- Lincoln Gunn scored 13 points to lead Princeton to an easy 60-46 win over Dominican on Sunday. Zach Finley had 12 points, eight rebounds and four blocked shots for the Tigers (3-12), who had a strong defensive performance against the Chargers (10-9). Will Carty had 12 points and three steals for Dominican, which made just 34 percent of its shots. The teams traded baskets early on, but Princeton took command midway through the first half, closing with a 24-6 run to take a 39-21 lead at the break. Princeton then continued its dominance in the second half, as the Chargers could not cut the deficit to less than 13 points. Princeton also won the battle of the boards, outrebounding Dominican 38-29.
